on, 07 Aug 2023 09:59:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/07/police-in-england-and-wales-will-pilot-project-to-shift-sexism-and-misogyny" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/07/mark-zuckerberg-not-holding-breath-for-cage-fight-with-elon-musk" target="_blank">Mark Zuckerberg not ‘holding breath’ for cage fight with Elon Musk</a></h2><div class="description"> Facebook co-founder posted on the Threads app that he was ‘ready today’ for a bout. He said he had suggested a date of 26 August for the contest. Zuckerberg said he is ‘not holding his breath’ over a proposed fight with Elon Musk.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 07:53:27 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/07/mark-zuckerberg-not-holding-breath-for-cage-fight-with-elon-musk" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/07/hsbc-executive-sherard-cowper-coles-apologises-uk-weak-china" target="_blank">HSBC executive apologises for calling UK weak over China</a></h2><div class="description"> Sherard Cowper-Coles said UK government was bowing to US demands in dealing with Beijing. The bank’s head of public affairs said sorry after ‘sharing his personal views’ at a private event. He said the UK government had caved in to the US in its approach to doing business with China.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 11:54:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/07/hsbc-executive-sherard-cowper-coles-apologises-uk-weak-china" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/06/at-least-two-people-said-to-have-declined-resignation-honours-from-liz-truss" target="_blank">At least two people said to have declined resignation honours from Liz Truss</a></h2><div class="description"> At least two people have reportedly turned down honours from Liz Truss' 14-strong list. One reportedly felt too ‘humiliated’ to accept a nomination from the UK’s shortest serving prime minister. The list is said to be currently being vetted by the House of Lords appointments commission.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 22:20:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/06/at-least-two-people-said-to-have-declined-resignation-honours-from-liz-truss" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/06/starmer-says-sunaks-lack-of-investment-in-wind-power-is-gift-to-putin" target="_blank">Starmer says Sunak’s lack of investment in wind power is ‘gift to Putin’</a></h2><div class="description"> Labour leader claims Conservatives’ onshore turbine ban costs families £180 each and makes UK reliant on gas imports. Starmer declares failure to invest in renewables such as wind turbines a ‘gift to Putin’ Labour leader also described onshore wind ban as ‘ludicrous’ and said it now means every family in the country is paying £180 more on energy bills.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 22:39:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/06/starmer-says-sunaks-lack-of-investment-in-wind-power-is-gift-to-putin" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/06/mps-paid-10m-for-second-jobs-and-freelance-work-over-past-year" target="_blank">MPs paid £10m for second jobs and freelance work over past year</a></h2><div class="description"> Boris Johnson’s extra income accounts for almost half of figure, of which vast majority was made by Tory MPs. Almost 18 months after furore around second jobs led to promises of a crackdown, MPs’ earnings from work outside parliament have continued to rise.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 17:00:16 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/06/mps-paid-10m-for-second-jobs-and-freelance-work-over-past-year" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/06/us-scientists-achieve-net-energy-gain-second-time-fusion-reaction" target="_blank">US scientists achieve net energy gain for second time in a fusion reaction</a></h2><div class="description"> The Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory’s National Ignition Facility achieved the feat using lasers to fuse two atoms. US scientists have achieved net energy gain in a nuclear fusion reaction for the second time since a historic breakthrough in December last year in the quest to find a near-limitless, safe and clean source of energy.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 23:31:10 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/06/us-scientists-achieve-net-energy-gain-second-time-fusion-reaction" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/07/saudi-aramcos-quarterly-profits-drop-nearly-40-but-it-still-rakes-in-30bn" target="_blank">Saudi Aramco’s quarterly profits drop nearly 40% but it still rakes in $30bn</a></h2><div class="description"> Decline in crude oil prices and less refining income trims revenues inflated in 2022 by Russian invasion of Ukraine. Company profits were $30.1bn for the months of April to June, down 38% from $48.4bn in the second quarter of last year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 09:51:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/07/saudi-aramcos-quarterly-profits-drop-nearly-40-but-it-still-rakes-in-30bn" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr