read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/07/a-locals-guide-to-reykjavik-iceland-the-best-bars-cafes-beaches-and-geothermal-pools" target="_blank">A local’s guide to Reykjavík, Iceland: the best bars, cafes, beaches and geothermal pools</a></h2><div class="description"> Downtown rents dropped because of the pandemic, lots of ambitious shops, cafes and restaurants launched as a result. There’s a real sense of revitalisation in the city. Artist Lilja Birgisdóttir on her favourite places for culture, eating out and bathing.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 06:00:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/07/a-locals-guide-to-reykjavik-iceland-the-best-bars-cafes-beaches-and-geothermal-pools" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/07/i-cant-get-allianz-to-refund-travel-insurance-though-my-partner-has-died" target="_blank">I can’t get Allianz to refund travel insurance though my partner has died</a></h2><div class="description"> I had to cancel a trip when my girlfriend died from cancer. I booked last summer, originally for April, at a cost of £3,228, plus £253 for travel insurance. We also paid an additional £220 premium for DM, who was in her early 80s with unrelated health conditions.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 06:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/07/i-cant-get-allianz-to-refund-travel-insurance-though-my-partner-has-died" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/07/niger-thousands-gather-for-rally-to-cheer-coup-generals-as-junta-closes-airspace-video-report" target="_blank">Niger: thousands gather for rally to cheer coup generals as junta closes airspace – video report</a></h2><div class="description"> Thousands of coup supporters in Niger gathered for a rally to cheer on the generals claiming power. A deadline set by the west African bloc for the military to relinquish control was due to elapse. The Ecowas bloc had given the troops that toppled President Mohamed Bazoum a week to return him to power.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 08:55:27 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/07/niger-thousands-gather-for-rally-to-cheer-coup-generals-as-junta-closes-airspace-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/01/bride-wades-through-floodwaters-after-philippines-hit-by-typhoons-video-report" target="_blank">Bride wades through floodwaters after Philippines hit by typhoons – video report</a></h2><div class="description"> The Philippines was hit with torrential rain over seven days, brought by Typhoon Doksuri and intensified by Typhoon Khanun. Low-lying villages to the north of the country were the worst affected. Residents were forced to travel by small wooden boats and roads were inundated.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 01 Aug 2023 12:10:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/01/bride-wades-through-floodwaters-after-philippines-hit-by-typhoons-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/31/wildfires-cross-us-border-into-canada-triggering-evacuation-order-video" target="_blank">Wildfires cross US border into Canada triggering evacuation order – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Canadian town of Osoyoos ordered to evacuate after wildfire crosses border from Washington state. Firefighters are using water cannon from planes to try to control the blaze, which is estimated to be 885 hectares (2,200 acres) in size. Local authorities estimate the blaze is 885-heater-size.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 31 Jul 2023 08:44:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/31/wildfires-cross-us-border-into-canada-triggering-evacuation-order-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/video/2023/jul/26/sinead-oconnor-the-turbulent-career-of-the-irish-sensation-video-obituary" target="_blank">The life and career of Sinéad O’Connor: ‘I was really a protest singer’ - video obituary</a></h2><div class="description"> Sinéad O'Connor has died at the age of 56, prompting grief and tributes. Irish singer abjured conventional stardom for most of her career. Some never forgave her for ripping up a picture of the pope on American TV. The Dubliner enjoyed something of a renaissance in recent years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 22:06:16 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/video/2023/jul/26/sinead-oconnor-the-turbulent-career-of-the-irish-sensation-video-obituary" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/27/drone-footage-shows-aftermath-of-wildfires-on-2500-year-old-sicilian-temple-video" target="_blank">Drone footage shows aftermath of wildfires on 2,500-year-old Sicilian temple – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The temple of Segesta has been turned to ash after days of fires spreading across Sicily. The island has been devastated by wildfires that have killed at least three people. Heatwaves and severe storms have also affected the north of Italy, while heatwaves and storms hit the north.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:44:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/27/drone-footage-shows-aftermath-of-wildfires-on-2500-year-old-sicilian-temple-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/greece-wildfires-break-out-corfu-thousands-flee-rhodes-blazes-video-report" target="_blank">Greece: wildfires rage on three islands and mainland – video report</a></h2><div class="description"> Firefighters struggling to contain 82 wildfires across the country, 64 of which started on Sunday, the hottest day of the summer so far. As well as huge blazes on Rhodes, 19,000 people were forced to flee the island of Rhodes. Wildfires also broke out on Corfu, Corfu and in the northern Peloponnese region.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 13:09:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/greece-wildfires-break-out-corfu-thousands-flee-rhodes-blazes-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/spain-faces-political-gridlock-after-national-elections-video-report" target="_blank">Spain faces political gridlock after national elections – video report</a></h2><div class="description"> Spain appears to be heading for political gridlock after rightwing parties fail to clinch a decisive victory. Pro-independence Catalan and Basque parties as potential kingmakers. Conservative People's party will be given first attempt at trying to cobble together enough votes to win a prime-ministerial investiture vote.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 12:11:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/spain-faces-political-gridlock-after-national-elections-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather and adds a further spurt of warmth to an already overheating world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">What you need to know about the 'extreme' heatwave hitting our oceans – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> Sea temperatures, particularly off the north-east coast of England and west of Ireland, are several degrees above normal, breaking records for late spring and early summer. The Met Office has said that according to records dating to 1850, global sea surface temperatures in April and May reached an all-time high.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 14:22:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/07/tell-us-about-the-lifestyle-changes-or-habits-you-have-adopted-to-stave-off-dementia" target="_blank">Tell us about the lifestyle changes or habits you have adopted to stave off dementia</a></h2><div class="description"> Jeremy Vine said he tries to prevent onset of dementia by listening to songs he hates. He said he was inspired to change his music habits after one of his friends said they were training their left hand to write in a bid to ward off dementia. We want to hear about the tips that have helped you in a way to prevent dementia.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 11:53:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/07/tell-us-about-the-lifestyle-changes-or-habits-you-have-adopted-to-stave-off-dementia" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/jul/31/tell-us-has-sewage-dumping-stopped-you-from-swimming-in-uk-seas" target="_blank">Tell us: has sewage dumping stopped you from swimming in UK seas?</a></h2><div class="description"> Poll found 23% of sea swimmers deterred by sewage discharges by water companies. Survey carried out by Savanta for the Liberal Democrats found that just over 30% said they usually went sea swimming during the summer. We want to hear from people living by the UK’s coasts.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 31 Jul 2023 13:03:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/jul/31/tell-us-has-sewage-dumping-stopped-you-from-swimming-in-uk-seas" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/07/uk-school-leavers-have-you-been-turned-off-university-over-affordability-concerns" target="_blank">UK school leavers: have you been turned off university over affordability concerns?</a></h2><div class="description"> We’re interested to hear from young Britons who have opted out of higher education because they feared student life would be unaffordable, or had concerns about their financial future if they attended university. Whether financial concerns relating to tuition fees, student accommodation, student loan repayments or concerns about graduate job prospects have prompted you to do an apprenticeship instead.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 09:57:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/07/uk-school-leavers-have-you-been-turned-off-university-over-affordability-concerns" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/03/tell-us-how-have-you-been-impcted-by-extreme-weather-in-britain" target="_blank">Tell us: how have you been impacted by extreme weather in the UK?</a></h2><div class="description"> 2023 has been a year of deadly extreme weather, from wildfires in Greece, Algeria and Canada to heatwaves in India and Texas. We want to hear how people have been affected by heatwaves, storms and flooding in the UK in the last few years. The UK will face a greater frequency of flash floods, winter storms and summer heatwaves.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 09:25:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/03/tell-us-how-have-you-been-impcted-by-extreme-weather-in-britain" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/07/how-hip-hop-gave-voice-to-a-generation-of-egyptians-hungry-for-change-podcast" target="_blank">How hip-hop gave voice to a generation of Egyptians hungry for change – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> From the early days of the Tahrir Square protests, music was vital to the young people making their voices heard. Though the country is taking another authoritarian turn, that spirit of dissent cannot be extinguished, says CNN's John Defterios. He says that despite the country's taking a turn, it is taking a new authoritarian turn.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 04:00:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/07/how-hip-hop-gave-voice-to-a-generation-of-egyptians-hungry-for-change-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/07/how-can-we-escape-burnout-podcast" target="_blank">How can we escape burnout? | Podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Burnout is a serious issue in workplaces across the UK. What can we do to change our working culture in order to prevent it? Lizzie, a nurse in Greater Manchester, says she recognised burnout as a sign of stress. She says it took another six months before she recognised it as burnout.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 02:00:27 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/07/how-can-we-escape-burnout-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/aug/05/weekend-podcast-at-home-with-world-heavyweight-champion-tyson-fury-john-crace-on-rishis-climate-retreat-and-comedian-michelle-brasier-on-befriending-her-scammer" target="_blank">Weekend podcast: at home with world heavyweight champion Tyson Fury, John Crace on Rishi’s climate retreat, and comedian Michelle Brasier on befriending her scammer</a></h2><div class="description"> Tyson Fury weighs in on marriage, mental health and life as a multimillionaire in Morecambe. John Crace looks on as the PM gaslights the UK with his North Sea plan while the world burns. Michelle Brasier explains why she befriended her scammer.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 04:00:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/aug/05/weekend-podcast-at-home-with-world-heavyweight-champion-tyson-fury-john-crace-on-rishis-climate-retreat-and-comedian-michelle-brasier-on-befriending-her-scammer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/aug/04/al-sharpton-on-60-years-since-the-civil-rights-march-on-washington-podcast" target="_blank">Al Sharpton on 60 years since the civil rights march on Washington – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> On 26 August, Rev Al Sharpton, Martin Luther King III, and other civil rights activists will commemorate the 1963 march on Washington. Jonathan Freedland sits down with Sharpton to discuss why he believes King's 'I have a dream' speech has been abused by some on the right. He also discusses why he is still fighting for police reform.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 04:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/aug/04/al-sharpton-on-60-years-since-the-civil-rights-march-on-washington-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/04/best-of-2023-so-far-battle-of-the-botanic-garden-the-horticulture-war-roiling-the-isle-of-wight-podcast" target="_blank">Best of 2023 … so far: Battle of the botanic garden: the horticulture war roiling the Isle of Wight – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Every Friday in August we will publish some of our favourite audio long reads of 2023. This week, from February, features a US businessman taking over a beloved garden. He decided on a radical new approach, all in the name of sustainability. But angry critics claim it’s just plain neglect.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/04/best-of-2023-so-far-battle-of-the-botanic-garden-the-horticulture-war-roiling-the-isle-of-wight-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/04/donald-trump-january-6-indictment-podcast" target="_blank">Donald Trump’s January 6 indictment - podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> The former US president appeared in court on Wednesday charged on four counts related to his efforts to overturn the result of the 2020 election. The former president faces four counts: conspiracy to defraud the United States; conspiracy to obstruct an official proceeding; obstruction of and attempt to obstruct a proceeding; and conspiracy against rights.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 02:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/04/donald-trump-january-6-indictment-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/03/underdogs-bite-back-as-germany-and-brazil-crash-out-womens-football-weekly" target="_blank">Underdogs bite back as Germany and Brazil crash out – Women’s Football Weekly</a></h2><div class="description"> Faye Carruthers is joined by Jo Khan, Chris Paouros and Claire Rafferty to wrap up an explosive final set of group games. The two-time world champions Germany are out of the World Cup, while Morocco make more history - the second lowest ranked team in the tournament are into the last 16.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 17:33:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/03/underdogs-bite-back-as-germany-and-brazil-crash-out-womens-football-weekly" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/07/brazilian-indigenous-reclaim-identities" target="_blank">‘I shout from the rooftops that I exist’: Brazil’s Indigenous people reclaim their identities</a></h2><div class="description"> The number of Brazilians who identify as Indigenous grew by nearly 90% in just 12 years. Being Indigenous was synonymous with being lazy, a good-for-nothing, a savage, said Vahnessa de Oliveira Ferreira, a tour guide and social educator who now identifies as a trans Indigenous woman.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 13:00:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/07/brazilian-indigenous-reclaim-identities" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/07/people-are-under-siege-why-ethiopias-war-in-tigray-isnt-over" target="_blank">‘People are under siege’: why Ethiopia’s war in Tigray isn’t over</a></h2><div class="description"> Father Tesfaye has shuttled between his home district of Irob and Mekelle, the capital of Ethiopia’s northern Tigray region. Despite a peace deal last November, Eritrean troops remain in some border areas, and the Irob community is paying the price. The Roman Catholic priest must take a treacherous back route through the mountains to avoid checkpoints.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 10:16:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/07/people-are-under-siege-why-ethiopias-war-in-tigray-isnt-over" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/trump-belief-2020-election-may-not-matter-obstruction-charge" target="_blank">Prosecutors may not need to show that Trump knew he had lost the election</a></h2><div class="description"> The obstruction of an official proceeding count may not turn on whether Trump believed his own claims. Based on a review of previous judicial rulings in other cases, it may not need to prove Trump knew he lost the election, as the former president’s legal team has repeatedly claimed.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 10:00:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/trump-belief-2020-election-may-not-matter-obstruction-charge" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/06/92-year-old-debanked-natwest-jamaica" target="_blank">‘Up all night worrying’: 92-year-old debanked by NatWest after move to Jamaica</a></h2><div class="description"> Philip Cato, a member of Windrush generation, emigrated to the UK in 1961. He moved 'home' in 1990s after 30 years working in the UK. Last year’s decision left him cut off from his state pension. Nigel Farage's account with Coutts was closed by NatWest last week.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 14:01:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/06/92-year-old-debanked-natwest-jamaica" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/07/lgbtq-southerners-face-new-damaging-laws" target="_blank">‘I look over my shoulder a little more’: LGBTQ+ people on surviving hostile laws in US south</a></h2><div class="description"> Louisiana legislators sent three bills targeting LGBTQ+ rights to Governor John Bel Edwards’s desk during the 2023 legislative session. Legislators have recently passed numerous anti-LGBTQ+ laws, but activists are buckling down and not giving in. “I love Louisiana,” said Peyton Rose Michelle, 25.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 09:00:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/07/lgbtq-southerners-face-new-damaging-laws" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/07/starwatch-get-ready-for-the-best-meteor-shower-of-the-year" target="_blank">Starwatch: get ready for the best meteor shower of the year</a></h2><div class="description"> The Perseid meteor shower is widely regarded as the best meteor shower of the year. Viewing conditions are good because the moon is in an advanced waning phase. The shower is active from mid-July through to the end of August, but peaks on the night of 12-13 August.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 05:00:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/07/starwatch-get-ready-for-the-best-meteor-shower-of-the-year" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Sign up for the Fashion Statement newsletter: our free fashion email</a></h2><div class="description"> Style, with substance: what’s really trending this week, a roundup of the best fashion journalism and your wardrobe dilemmas solved, delivered straight to your inbox every Thursday. Find out what's really trending and what you need to look at this week's top fashion stories.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 20 Sep 2022 11:06:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2019/jul/09/sign-up-for-word-of-mouth-the-best-of-guardian-food-every-week" target="_blank">Sign up for Word of Mouth: the best of Guardian Food every week</a></h2><div class="description"> A weekly email bringing you our best food writing, the latest recipes, seasonal eating ideas and must-read restaurant reviews. Sign up below to start receiving the best of our culinary journalism in one mouth-watering weekly email. We'll send you latest recipes from Yotam Ottolenghi, Nigel Slater, Meera Sodha and all our star cooks.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 09 Jul 2019 08:19:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2019/jul/09/sign-up-for-word-of-mouth-the-best-of-guardian-food-every-week" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/gallery/2023/aug/07/a-cat-in-a-drier-and-a-dog-in-the-driving-seat-mondays-best-photos" target="_blank">A cat in a drier and a dog in the driving seat: Monday’s best photos</a></h2><div class="description"> The Guardian’s picture editors select photo highlights from around the world. The Guardian's photo highlights are selected by the Guardian's picture editors each week to highlight the best of the day. In the world's top 10 photos, please submit your best for next week's top ten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 12:52:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/gallery/2023/aug/07/a-cat-in-a-drier-and-a-dog-in-the-driving-seat-mondays-best-photos" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/gallery/2023/aug/07/a-ceasefire-in-tigray-but-in-the-displaced-peoples-camps-the-suffering-goes-on-in-pictures" target="_blank">A ceasefire in Tigray, but in the displaced peoples’ camps, the suffering goes on – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> About 1.8 million people were displaced because of fighting in the northern Ethiopian region. Ximena Borrazás and Edgar Gutierrez got rare access to the camps where many people are still struggling to get enough food to survive. Despite an end to fighting, many people still struggle to find food.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 06:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/gallery/2023/aug/07/a-ceasefire-in-tigray-but-in-the-displaced-peoples-camps-the-suffering-goes-on-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/